==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perigone
<hw>Per"i*gone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>peri-</ets> + Gr. <?/ productive organs.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any organ inclosing the essential
organs of a flower; a perianth.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In mosses, the
involucral bracts of a male flower.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A sac which surrounds the
generative bodies in the gonophore of a hydroid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perigonium</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
